# KadirOS Design System Rules

## Window Sizing
- ALWAYS use `max-w-4xl` or `max-w-5xl` for windows (never larger)
- ALWAYS use `max-h-[calc(100vh-12rem)] md:max-h-[75vh]` pattern
- Window headers: `h-10`, padding `px-3 py-2`

## Typography
- Headings: `text-lg md:text-xl` (H1), `text-base md:text-lg` (H2), `text-sm` (H3)
- Body text: `text-xs` (normal), `text-[10px]` (small), `text-[9px]` (tiny)
- Window titles: `text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.1em]`

## Spacing
- Window body padding: `p-3 md:p-4`
- Panel padding: `p-2 md:p-3`
- Gaps: `gap-2` or `gap-1.5` between items, `gap-3 md:gap-4` between sections

## Icons
- Window header: 16px
- Section headers: 14px
- Buttons: 12px-16px
- Display: 40px-48px

## Colors
- Primary: `#25f4f4` (text-primary)
- Background: `#102222` (bg-background-dark)
- Surface: `#152a2a` (bg-surface-dark)

## Component Patterns
- Scrollable containers: `flex-1 overflow-y-auto min-h-0`
- Flex containers: Always add `min-h-0` to prevent overflow issues
- Fixed elements: Use `flex-shrink-0`

## Responsive
- Mobile-first approach
- Use `md:` prefix for tablet+ (768px+)
- Padding always responsive: `p-2 md:p-3` or `p-3 md:p-4`

## DO NOT
- Don't use `h-screen` or `h-full` on windows
- Don't use padding larger than `p-4`
- Don't use font sizes larger than `text-xl`
- Don't create windows wider than `max-w-5xl`

